"{\"uid\": \"wwd.com-fashion-news-fashion-scoops-stella-jean-designs-uniforms-team-haiti-2024-paris-olympics-1236373506\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Today's Digital Daily  Today's Digital Daily  Aimed at celebrating the cultural richness of the troubled Caribbean country, the uniforms will make their official debut on July 26 at the 2024 Paris Olympics Opening Ceremony.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Milan Correspondent  STELLA'S HOPE:Haitian-Italiandesigner Stella Jean, an early advocate and champion of diversity and inclusivity in fashion, is creating uniforms for Team Haiti at theParis Olympicsscheduled for July 26 to Aug. 11.\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 225, \"end\": 230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 0.999999998027306, \"rank\": 1.9720930798899577e-09, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 15-athlete team is to sport the uniforms conceived by Jean at the opening ceremony to be held on July 26 along the River Seine in Paris.You May Also Like  The tie-up marks an opportunity for Jean to spotlight her native country, its artisanship and cultural richness, which recently had been overshadowed by immense political instability in the country, crime, deadly natural disasters and the consequences of the \\\"double debt,\\\" the fashion company said in a statement.Related ArticlesEye ScoopsThe Milano Cortina 2026 Olympic and Paralympic Torch UnveiledFashion FeaturesShaun White's Snow League Lines Up Hublot, Tiffany, Other Brands  Jean has linked with Haitian painter Philippe Dodard, whose artwork titled \\\"Passage\\\" is to be incorporated in the uniforms.\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 1225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 579, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 963, \"end\": 982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2026_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Milano Cortina 2026\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2026_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2026_Winter_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 963, \"end\": 982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2026_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Milano Cortina 2026\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2026_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2026_Winter_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1123, \"end\": 1130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999801452761, \"rank\": 1.9854799669377283e-08, \"text\": \"Haitian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}, {\"begin\": 1139, \"end\": 1154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Dodard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippe Dodard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Dodard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Dodard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's version features a full skirt bearing Dodard's artworks paired with a chambray shirt, woven in Haiti as part of the country's tradition in spinning the so-called \\\"blue cotton,\\\" a heritage that is progressively dying out.\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1334, \"end\": 1339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.504345405930361e-20, \"text\": \"Haiti\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Layered on top is a sleeveless blazer crafted from recycled fabric to which the HaitianOlympicemblem is pinned.\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1571, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's uniform has pants that feature the Dodard painting's motif paired with a field jacket inspired by the signature Haitian shirt Guayabera, worn by local men, a nod to Jean's grandfather, the company said.\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999801452761, \"rank\": 1.9854799669377283e-08, \"text\": \"Haitian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}, {\"begin\": 1709, \"end\": 1718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guayabera\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guayabera\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guayabera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guayabera\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The jacket will be worn atop a striped shirt and accessorized with a printed scarf.\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Haiti is enduring one of its worst periods of chaos.\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 1923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1871, \"end\": 1876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.504345405930361e-20, \"text\": \"Haiti\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the assassination of its president Jovenel Mo\\u00efse in 2021, local gangs have recently shut down the airport and looted seaports, public buildings and shops and targeted several police stations, especially in and around Port-au-Prince, the country's capital, currently under a state of emergency.\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 2223, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1965, \"end\": 1978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jovenel_Mo\\u00efse\", \"score\": 0.9921317369203713, \"rank\": 0.0079306633433392, \"text\": \"Jovenel Mo\\u00efse\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jovenel_Mo\\u00efse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jovenel_Mo\\u00efse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prime Minister Ariel Henry has been stranded in Puerto Rico as gang members demand his resignation.\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2239, \"end\": 2250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariel_Henry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariel Henry\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariel_Henry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariel_Henry\"}, {\"begin\": 2272, \"end\": 2283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico\", \"score\": 0.9999999984888746, \"rank\": 1.510710127895128e-09, \"text\": \"Puerto Rico\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 15 athletes competing in the upcoming Olympics are, according to Jean's statement, \\\"standard bearers of peace [who] will have an even more demanding task than arriving to the podium as medal recipients.\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2531, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are 15 living symbols of rebirth and renewal that extend beyond what is usually shown.\\\"\", \"from\": 2532, \"to\": 2624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The uniforms created by Jean will be exhibited at the Haitian National Pantheon Museum, known as Mupanah, in Port-au-Prince.\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 2750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2680, \"end\": 2687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999801452761, \"rank\": 1.9854799669377283e-08, \"text\": \"Haitian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], 